This file contains all lists of commands in vi editor
A) vi is in two modes ie command mode and insert mode.
B) To navigate on command mode the following commands can be used
     1) esc to exit insert mode.
     2) i to enter insert mode.
     3) :q! to quit vi without saving.
     4) :wq to quit after saving vi.
     5) hjkl to move around the cursor.
     6) x to delete current letter.
     7) X to delete letter on the right.
     8) dd to delete a whole line.
     9) nyy to copy text or line.
     10 P,P to paste.
